                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-17T23:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1916, 11 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 18, 1 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3361. I have never been informed about your negotiations about <hi rend="italic"
                        >Lusitania</hi>, but (?) if there is delay, it is owing to the fact that
                    Germany is unwilling to admit obligation to pay indemnity, while possibly
                    willing to pay indemnity in this case. I have gathered this in informal
                    conversation with members of Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
